        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 8:43AM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 843 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Dancyville, or 14 miles south of Brownsville, moving northeast at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Asbury, Yum Yum, Stanton, Brownsville, Belmont, Hickory Point,
Uptonville, Taylor Chapel, Shepp, Whiteville, Meux Corner, Fayette
Corners, Laconia, Hillville, Cedar Chapel, Vildo, Hatchie, Moorman,
Sunnyhill, and Morton Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
